\begin_layout Section
Some Tips
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Some recommendations from Graham Stephan:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Don't fall in love with your investment property!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Always buy property that has significant upside potential - improvements,
 and so on.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Long-term outlook and fixed-term loan.
 Buy once and hold.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Cash-flow first!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Be friendly, but not friends!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Have cash reserves from 3-6 months, and some reserves for repairs and mortgage.
 (Graham is using checking account)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Don't pick a bad tenant!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Leaks are # 1 things that need fixing ASAP - have a plumber available!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stick to the contract! Strict responsibilities on landlord's side and tenant's
 side.
 Find and buy good and durable things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Anything that can break ...
 will break! Beautiful shiny expensive glass, door, ...
 you need to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

baby-proof
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 the house.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Bathroom ceiling fan must be turn on at the same time as lights automatically
 - otherwise, sooner or later, moisture's gonna build up in the bathroom
 and that's going to create mold.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Graham doesn't like condos he prefers single family houses, duplexes, or
 triplexes, so 2-4 units.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
90% of properties suck and produce no cash-flow.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Don't buy investing property
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Flat <30m2 and with no sinking fund and no management.
 Also try to avoid high void areas (over supply and under demand).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In areas with declining population.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Don't buy property in which you can't add value in it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Don't buy property that will not give you any cash flow or low ROI.
\end_layout

